Full Description: As of January 29, 2007, Yak Communications, Inc. was acquired by OneConnect Services Inc. Yak Communications, Inc., a switch-based reseller, provides telecommunications services in Canada and the United States. It operates through five segments: Yak Canada, Yak for Business, Contour, Yak America, and WorldCity VoIP. The Yak Canada segment offers 10-10-Yak, a variable dial-around long distance product; yakLongDistance, a Ã¢â‚¬Ëœ1+' pre-subscribed long distance service; yakCell, a pre-subscribed two stage dialing service for cell-phone users; yakCallingCard, a post-paid phone card service for travelers; and LooneyCall, a flat-rate long distance dial-around service. The Yak for Business segment provides various voice and data products, including local lines, long distance services, and data and Internet services to small and medium-sized businesses in Canada. The Contour segment provides outsourced managed telecommunications services from the review and technology planning stage, to the implementation and administration stage, to the support services stage. The Yak America segment provides various long distance voice products to residential customers located in the United States, as well as provides interstate and intrastate residential long distance services. WorldCity VoIP segment provides VoIP services to residential customers located in the United States, Canada and other international locations. This segment provides yakToAnyone, a prepaid VoIP service, which allows users to make PC to PSTN Internet phone calls over a high-speed connection; and yakUnlimited, a pre-subscribed VoIP service, which allows users to make North American Internet phone calls. The company was founded in 1998 and is based in Toronto, Canada with additional offices in Miami, Florida and Brossard, Canada.

Description: Midas Touch is a market leader in high-end VR games and technology.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Midas Touch is a market leader in high-end VR games and technology. Their goal is to bring advanced physics simulation engines that enable true to life, immediate interaction to the nascent virtual reality (VR) industry. They have created a cutting edge physics engine named "Midas Physics Engine" to accomplish this, and they are using it to build their own VR games to show off its power and potential. The current generation of VR content focuses on the loose interaction between players and the virtual environment, be it a gadget, a gun, a house, or a scenic landscape. The next generation of VR will foster a much closer interaction between players and the virtual characters. This will be powered by advanced physics simulation technology that will significantly enhance interactivity and invoke strong emotions in players. Research shows that a VR world governed by the same laws of physics as the real world brings a visceral feeling of immersion to players who interact with it. The next generation of VR doesnâ€™t have a ready to use physics engine yet. The world lacks a high fidelity physics simulation engine that addresses all the key requirements of VR to make the virtual reality world feel real: - Physics Driven Characters -  Instead of keyframes, characters are driven by AI and physics simulation which makes them react realistically to every touch and interaction. - Jitter free and explosion free simulation - Their joints are rock steady, prevent positions from flickering inconsistently, and never let parts explode. Without Midas Physics Engine, VR will have physical inconsistencies that will instantly destroy the illusion of reality that is critical to the user experience. - Complex Articulation Structures - Midas Physics Engine can handle modeling complex real world objects like chains, ropes, cranes, and other highly interconnected objects. Mere box colliders are not enough give virtual worlds the feeling of being real.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Gaming, Hardware, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: Haunted Ozarks was started in 2010 as a haunted attraction unlike anything in our area.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Haunted Ozarks was started in 2010 as a haunted attraction unlike anything in our area.  Using Hollywood level sets and expertly trained actors, Haunted Ozarks quickly became one of the top haunted attractions in the Branson/Springfield area in the first year.  Awarded the 2nd best haunted attraction in the Oklahoma/Missouri/Texas area in 2011, Haunted Ozarks soon became a destination for tourists from as far away as Illinois and Colorado.  We have a dedicated fan base with over 3,000 likes on our Facebook page and visitors posting rave reviews.  What makes Haunted Ozarks unique is our dedication to never giving our audience the same product every year.  We have changed our maze layout and design from year to year which gives our returning customers something new every season they visit.   Two of our partners are screenwriters with numerous options, so we are always striving to deliver Hollywood style thrills to our patrons.  In 2013 we partnered with Fox Television and created an attraction showcasing their new show "Sleepy Hollow" and helped them promote the show's debut season.   Haunted Ozarks is also dedicated to being involved in the community and local charities.  We particularly enjoy assisting charities that aid children and teenagers since these are our primary customer base.  We have donated tickets to the Boys and Girls club, as well as Big Brothers and Sisters.  We have also held food drives for Christian Action Ministries and held dedicated non scary trick or treating nights for smaller children.  We also offer military discounts and have dedicated nights for veterans and their families.   Owners Joe Blackerby, Lewis Holleman and Grant Smith are all dedicated to their families and include them in this community event that has entertained thousands over the last 4 years.

Full Description: USC Annenberg Center on Communication Leadership and Policy focuses on issues including communication technology, mobile innovation, and social change. The technological, sociological and regulatory landscape opens avenues for information even as it challenges longstanding media infrastructure. Navigating this shifting terrain to reach higher ground requires the guidance of seasoned and innovative scholars and professionals provoking thought and discourse, and educating policymakers, industry leaders and the public. It is a source of research and analysis, dialogue and instruction on communication leadership, CCLP is helping shape the future of news, information and civic discourse.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Education, Media and Entertainment, Navigation and Mapping
